Data collected by Chuck and Carol Rubow.  Sky clear- bright sun.  Slight breeze from south. Slight ripple on lake surface.

Data collected by Chuck and Carol Rubow.  Partly cloudy- sun not visible most of tne time.  Moderate breeze from south. Lake surface moderately choppy.  Anchor would not hold boat over Deep Hole- resulting in cable/rope being approximately 10 degrees off plumb.  Also- it was discovered after returning to shore that depth markings on Secchi Disk and D.O. water sampler were short by about 1 inch per foot (rope had shrunk over time )  Recorded data is in terms of markings on rope.

Data collected by Chuck and Carol Rubow.  Hazy sun.  Very slight breeze.  Slight ripple on lake surface. Recorded data from Secchi Disk and D.O. water sampler is in terms of depth markings on ropes. See comments re 06/24/2007 data.

Data collected by Chuck and Carol Rubow.  Sunny- cloudless sky.  Slight breeze. slight ripple on lake surface.  Due to replacement of faulty temperature probe cable with new 80 foot cable- temperature data was taken only to a depth of 80 feet.  Also- due to a personal interruption- color comparisons of the D.O. samples were not made until the following day- at which time they were all identical (10).  Water samples were then recollected at 40 and 85 feet- and checked using two extra CHEMets vials which happened to be with the monitoring apparatus.  Color comparisons relating to these samples both resulted in readings of 2.  Because of questions about the accuracy of this data- it has not been entered.
